<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="69073" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="69073">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="69073">
We tentatively identified specimens collected in this study as ssp. 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Tajuria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Tajuria sekii subsp. cooperi" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="69073" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="sekii" subSpecies="cooperi">Tajuria sekii cooperi</taxonomicName>
, with the bluish scales in the centre of fore-wings absent and a relatively limited violet area on hind-wings.
</paragraph>
